{"title":"Lecture 1: Combinatorial Foundations of Probability","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Lecture 1: Combinatorial Foundations of Probability","author":"Carlos Buitrago","format":{"html":{"toc":true},"pdf":{"toc":true}}},"headingText":"Motivation","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n<div style=\"\npadding:20px 0;\nborder-bottom:3px solid #2563eb;\nmargin-bottom:25px;\n\">\n\n<h1 style=\"\nmargin:0;\nfont-size:60px;\nfont-weight:900;\ncolor:#111827;\nfont-family:Arial,sans-serif;\n\">\nSeminar 1\n</h1>\n\n<p style=\"\nmargin:8px 0 0 0;\nfont-size:22px;\ncolor:#6b7280;\n\">\nProbability Theory by\n<span style=\"\nfont-family:Georgia, serif;\nfont-style:italic;\nfont-size:26px;\ncolor:#374151;\n\">\nCarlos Buitrago\n</span>\n· Fall 2026\n</p>\n\n</div>\n\n\n\nProbability starts with counting.\n\nIf all outcomes are equally likely,\n\n$$\nP(A)=\\frac{|A|}{|\\Omega|}.\n$$\n\nTherefore, many probability problems reduce to counting.\n\n## Example\n\nA password consists of 4 digits.\n\nHow many passwords exist?\n\nWe have\n\n$$\n10^4=10000.\n$$\n\nThe probability of guessing correctly in one attempt is\n\n$$\n\\frac{1}{10000}.\n$$\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n<div style=\"\npadding:20px 0;\nborder-bottom:3px solid #2563eb;\nmargin-bottom:25px;\n\">\n\n<h1 style=\"\nmargin:0;\nfont-size:60px;\nfont-weight:900;\ncolor:#111827;\nfont-family:Arial,sans-serif;\n\">\nSeminar 1\n</h1>\n\n<p style=\"\nmargin:8px 0 0 0;\nfont-size:22px;\ncolor:#6b7280;\n\">\nProbability Theory by\n<span style=\"\nfont-family:Georgia, serif;\nfont-style:italic;\nfont-size:26px;\ncolor:#374151;\n\">\nCarlos Buitrago\n</span>\n· Fall 2026\n</p>\n\n</div>\n\n\n# Motivation\n\nProbability starts with counting.\n\nIf all outcomes are equally likely,\n\n$$\nP(A)=\\frac{|A|}{|\\Omega|}.\n$$\n\nTherefore, many probability problems reduce to counting.\n\n## Example\n\nA password consists of 4 digits.\n\nHow many passwords exist?\n\nWe have\n\n$$\n10^4=10000.\n$$\n\nThe probability of guessing correctly in one attempt is\n\n$$\n\\frac{1}{10000}.\n$$\n"},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":false,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"jupyter"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true},"pandoc":{"standalone":true,"wrap":"none","default-image-extension":"png","to":"html","toc":true,"number-sections":true,"output-file":"Seminar01_Counting.html"},"language":{"toc-title-document":"Table of contents","toc-title-website":"On this page","related-formats-title":"Other Formats","related-notebooks-title":"Notebooks","source-notebooks-prefix":"Source","other-links-title":"Other Links","code-links-title":"Code Links","launch-dev-container-title":"Launch Dev Container","launch-binder-title":"Launch Binder","article-notebook-label":"Article Notebook","notebook-preview-download":"Download Notebook","notebook-preview-download-src":"Download Source","notebook-preview-bac